- 'costly maintenance activities' refers to activities with a cost amount greater than 500;
- 'preceded by a failure mode' means the failure occurred before the maintenance activity;
- 'details' include the asset name, maintenance activity name, cost amount, currency, cost category, maintenance date, failure mode name, and failure date.

- 'Flowers' represent assets;
- 'Withered flowers' represent assets that have failed;
- 'Gardeners' represent maintenance activities;
- 'Tended to' means the assets have associated maintenance activities.

sql:
SELECT failure_mode_name
FROM failure_modes
WHERE failure_mode_id = 1;

SELECT a.asset_name
FROM assets a
WHERE a.asset_id IN (
    SELECT ama.asset_id
    FROM asset_maintenance_activities ama
    INNER JOIN costs c ON ama.maintenance_activity_id = c.maintenance_activity_id
) AND a.asset_id IN (
    SELECT afm.asset_id
    FROM asset_failure_modes afm
);

SELECT COUNT(asset_id) 
FROM asset_failure_modes 
WHERE asset_id = 1;

